title: Mourners gather for American killed by cartel on Mexico trip
description: One of the two Americans gunned down three weeks ago by a Mexican cartel is being remembered as a sweet man who hoped to celebrate his birthday with a journey over the border

title: Ruling halts oil exports from Iraq's Kurdish area via Turkey
description: Iraqi officials announced Saturday that Baghdad has won an international arbitration case that will halt oil exports from the semi-autonomous Kurdish region by way of Turkey

title: Ex-Navy swimmer tried to drown security guard, officials say
description: A former Navy rescue swimmer is charged with attempted murder after Florida authorities say he tried to drown a security guard

title: Mexico sanctioned for not protecting endangered porpoise
description: Mexico faces sanctions from the international wildlife body known as CITES for not doing enough to protect the vaquita marina, a small porpoise that is the world's most endangered marine mammal

title: Violent clash between French police, demonstrators at anti-reservoir protest
description: Dozens were reportedly injured as police clashed with environmental activists protesting a giant agricultural irrigation reservoir being built in rural western France.

title: Nicholas Lloyd Webber, son of famed composer, dies at 43
description: Nicholas Lloyd Webber, the Grammy-nominated composer, record producer and eldest son of Andrew Lloyd Webber, died Saturday in England

title: Putin says Russia will station tactical nukes in Belarus
description: Russian President Vladimir Putin has announced plans to station tactical nuclear weapons in neighboring Belarus

title: Israel: 2 soldiers wounded in West Bank drive-by shooting
description: The Israeli military says two soldiers were wounded, one severely, in a drive-by shooting in the occupied West Bank, the latest in months-long violence between Israel and the Palestinians

title: Snowfall, heavy rain in Afghanistan kill at least 3
description: An Afghan government spokesman says snowfall and heavy rain have killed at least three people, including a child

title: WATCH:  At least 23 killed after powerful tornado ripped through Mississippi
description: Millions are on alert for tornadoes, damaging winds and flooding.

title: Rate hikes hammer some consumers. Relief may be coming, experts say.
description: Rate hikes have ballooned loan costs. Relief may be coming, experts say.

title: New Zealand tells China its concern on lethal aid to Russia
description: New Zealand Foreign Minister Nanaia Mahuta has expressed concern to China over any provision of lethal aid to support Russia in its war against Ukraine during a meeting with her Chinese counterpart

title: 7 dead in Mississippi tornado, official says
description: This is a developing story.

title: Bank failures and rescue test Yellen's decades of experience
description: Treasury Secretary Janet Yellen worked against the clock with other regulators, lawmakers and business leaders to come up with a plan that would prevent a full blown banking crisis

title: Greene's DC jail visit pulls GOP closer to Jan. 6 rioters
description: Rep_ Marjorie Taylor Greene swept into the District of Columbia jail to check on conditions for the Jan_ 6 detainees, who chanted “Let’s Go Brandon!”

title: 2 dead, 9 missing after explosion at chocolate factory
description: Two people are dead, 9 are missing and multiple others are injured after an explosion at a chocolate factory Friday in West Reading, Pennsylvania.

title: Gordon Moore, co-founder and former chairman of Intel, dies at 94
description: Gordon Moore, the co-founder and former chairman of tech giant Intel, died Friday at the age of 94, the company and the Gordon and Betty Moore Foundation announced.

title: 8 injured in smoky blast at Pennsylvania chocolate factory
description: Firefighters battled a blaze in Pennsylvania after an explosion at a chocolate factory injured at least eight people and sent a plume of black smoke into the air above West Reading

title: Los Angeles public school district, service workers reach bargaining agreement
description: The Los Angeles public school district reached a "historic" agreement with its Service Employees International Union Local 99 on Friday, the district announced.

title: Short on planes, American will suspend some flights to Spain
description: American Airlines will suspend some flights to Europe this spring because of a delay in getting new planes from Boeing

title: Sheriff: 2 dead in Southern California helicopter crash
description: Authorities say two people have died in a helicopter crash in Southern California

title: 'Numerous' migrants reported injured in train car in Texas: Police
description: Medical helicopters responded to an area on U.S. Highway 90 near Knippa, Texas, "due to numerous undocumented immigrants injured inside of a train cart," police said.
